#59 Add Content to Natural Language Processing Basics

div.div:
Hey @pratik-99! Welcome to Data Science Notes 😊
So currently, the basics page for the NLP section is blank, so adding anything useful would be a big help! This could be basics of NLP like stemming, bag of words, tokenization, etc or even an outline that contains all the different basic topics that can be filled in later on.
Essentially, anything that you think would be a helpful basic of NLP would be great to add! If you have a more specific in-depth topic in NLP then that would be best suited for a new page, however, if you'd like to explain some general basics, then this is perfect!
It is super easy to add content; it can be in markdown, jupyter notebooks, or other formats as discussed [***here***](https://github.com/wyattowalsh/data-science-notes/blob/master/FORMATTING.md)
Please let me know if you have any issues or questions; I'm happy to help out! 👍
